plot: Film noir parody with a detective uncovering a sinister plot. Characters from real noirs appear as scenes from various films are intercut.
title: Dead Men Don't Wear Plaid

plot: A brain surgeon marries a femme fatale, causing his life to turn upside down. Things go more awry when he falls in love with a talking brain.
title: The Man with Two Brains

plot: The fates of several people are intertwining randomly. Their sympathy of each other faces multiple differences in their lifestyles.
title: Grand Canyon

plot: The rivalry between two gangs, the poor Greasers and the rich Socs, only heats up when one gang member kills a member of the other.
title: The Outsiders

plot: In 1935, Indiana Jones arrives in India, still part of the British Empire, and is asked to find a mystical stone. He then stumbles upon a secret cult committing enslavement and human sacrifices in the catacombs of an ancient palace.
title: Indiana Jones and the Temple of Doom

plot: The Fellowship of the Ring embark on a journey to destroy the One Ring and end Sauron's reign over Middle-earth.
title: The Lord of the Rings

plot: In a totalitarian future society, a man, whose daily work is re-writing history, tries to rebel by falling in love.
A man awakens from a coma to discover he has a psychic ability.
title: The Dead Zone

plot: A group of people try to survive when machines start to come alive and become homicidal.
title: Maximum Overdrive

plot: A mysterious new shop opens in a small town which always seems to stock the deepest desires of each shopper, with a price far heavier than expected.
title: Needful Things

plot: Cujo, a friendly St. Bernard, contracts rabies and conducts a reign of terror on a small American town.
title: Cujo

plot: A young couple is trapped in a remote town where a dangerous religious cult of children believes that everyone over age 18 must be killed.
title: Children of the Corn

plot: A canine angel, Charlie, sneaks back to earth from heaven but ends up befriending an orphan girl who can speak to animals. In the process, Charlie learns that friendship is the most heavenly gift of all.
title: All Dogs Go to Heaven
